animal.description:
Meet Gracie! 

She’s a 9 year old, 65lb love bug. 
Gracie is the perfect age to be trained and over all the annoying puppy stuff, but young and spunky enough to play and accompany you on walks if you’d like. If you would rather hang out on the couch all day, she’d be up for that too! Gracie is really easy going and not hard to please. 

This pretty girl had multiple mast cell tumors removed while in our care. While they are always removed with clear margins and come back low grade, it’s important that an adopter stay vigilant if / when new masses pop up. The key to keeping her healthy for as long as possible will be early detection and removal. You will also need to continue tending to her ongoing allergies. She currently receives Cytopoint injections and takes a daily medication to help with her itching. 

Gracies ideal home is one with no other pets. She has attended a professional group training class and learned a lot, which her foster continues to build on at home. Her adopter will need to continue working with her overreaction and leash frustration regarding seeing other dogs while on walks. 

Gracie is very well mannered in the home and is fully house and crate trained. She enjoys hanging out with her foster mom (she is an under the cover type of snuggle bug) and taking walks. She is quiet and is non destructive. 

If you’d like to open your home to this very deserving senior gal, please apply at www.mercysdoorpetrescue.org. Gracies adoption fee is $100, and she has been spayed, vaccinated, microchipped, HW- and is on monthly flea/tick/HW prevention.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Tonka has come to rescue with her bonded male, Tank from San Antonio, Texas. They were dumped and picked up as strays by the shelter to be euthanized. The Right to Live Rescue contacted us about these 2 and pulled them and got them on a transport to Casper, WY. They are a pair of older, gentle giants who need some TLC in their lives. They are both curious and approach to check you out. Once you hang out with them, you will find that they are very sweet and will make perfect snuggle buddies. Will you give them loving homes to live out their senior years in? Tank and Tonka are both around 8 years old, the vet says she thinks Tank is older just by his outward apperance, but overall is healthy, in spite of the HW and 2 torn ACL's that went untreated. The eyes just needed to be cleaned to stop the constant irritation. . Tank is Heartworm Positive and is being treated with Heartgard, the slow kill method. We put Tank and Tonka on Cosequin DS and both are doing so much better. Tank gets up and down better and enjoys frolicking in the grass and rolling over and over. They both enjoyed their baths and will get you some new pics

animal.description:
Fiona is STILL waiting for a forever home! She came to us as part of a cruelty case at 3 months old after being found next to an apartment building. She had been confined to a small kennel for 3 days without food or water. She was emaciated and couldn’t even stand due to malnutrition and dehydration. Her amazing foster mom nursed her back to health and has loved Fiona as her own while waiting for a forever home to come along. 

Fiona is approximately 3 year old, fixed, UTD on shots, and microchipped. She would do best in a home with a male dog her size or larger or as an only dog. Fenced yard REQUIRED. Fiona would do best in a home with kids 8+ years old.

From Fiona’s foster mom:
"...Fiona is crate trained, house trained, knows basic obedience & loves kids. She is fearful of men but has come a long way & is a total love when she trusts you. She is dog selective. Fiona is a sweet girl that just needs a home with a little patience..." 

www.facebook.com/loxanimalrescuecomm

animal.description:
Smokey is shy with people, but he loves walks and food so that is the key to his heart. He needs time to get comfortable in new places and with new people, but he will accept treats and warm up quickly. He is not yet comfortable being petted or handled by people, but he loves doing activities with other dogs and learning from them. Smokey absolutely adores other dogs here at the Sanctuary. He is very active and playful when he's around them, and they help him build his confidence. 
Smokey was born in 2014 and came to Best Friends from a humane society in Idaho. He can jump fences, so he is considered a flight risk. In a former foster home, he was a bit of an escape artist, so he will need a home with a secure enclosure and someone with a watchful eye. At the Sanctuary, he is working on crate training, getting into and riding in a car and getting more comfortable with new places. He already walks well on a leash.
Smokey will need some time to adjust to a new home, but with time and patience he will make a wonderful companion.

animal.description:
Sundance's name fits him perfectly. He has a unique personality that will make you fall in love with him. He also dances with excitement when he's happy to see you. He is shy and fearful with strangers, but once he knows you, he will always greet you with a smile and gaze at you in a loving way. He can be a little quirky, and his caregivers say he is like a wiggly cat in a dog's body, but that's what makes him so endearing.
Born in 2013, Sundance came to the Sanctuary from a Best Friends Network Partner in Indiana. He is incredibly smart and knows what he wants and doesn't want. He will guard food and is not comfortable with strangers entering his room or yard if he doesn't know them so he would do better meeting them outside of his area first. animal.description:
Skelly came to Best Friends as a puppy mom. Over time, Skelly has made a lot of progress at the sanctuary. When she arrived she had a hard time trusting anyone to touch her, let alone leash her. Now she trusts her caregivers enough to let them leash her up and take her for walks on the trails, which she loves. She is starting to explore new places such as Dogtown's indoor agility area and the offices in Dogtown headquarters, where she can experience a more home-like environment. 
A good way to build trust with Skelly is through hand feeding her meals. She is still too nervous to ride in a car, but she is working on it. She will sometimes eat her meals near a car, which helps her to see that it's not so scary. She also is working on crate training. One of Skelly's favorite things is to visit our one acre dog park where she can run and explore in a safe way. She oftentimes runs off and explores and later comes back to follow her caregiver around and get treats. 
Because she is still very nervous during medical handling and grooming, Skelly is trained to wear a muzzle during these appointments. She does allow her trusted people to handle her and examine her as needed. 
Skelly has play dates with other dogs at the Sanctuary, and she has been easygoing with all the dogs she's met. She's also been a good walking buddy for other dogs. She does tend to be a little sensitive and will squeal sometimes if a dog is too rough, so she should live with dogs who understand that and won't scare her. Although she can be hand fed by those she trusts, Skelly does guard food bowls from people. She has learned to trade them for other items she wants, like treats. She can also be territorial if she doesn't know a person and will protect her space, including her beds and toys. 
Skelly is looking for a person or family who will take the time to earn her trust and not rush her. A home with a friendly dog would also help her adjust.
animal.name: Skelly

animal.description:
Kaeli is shy with strangers, and it takes some time for her to get comfortable with them. At Dogtown she has a special routine to follow when being introduced to a new person. Once she gets to know people, she absolutely loves them. Sometimes she wants to be close to you, getting lots of attention, and other times she would just prefer to hang out and do her own thing. 
She loves walks and turns them into casual strolls, because she loves to take in all the sights and smells at her own pace. She really loves new toys and will show them off by getting the 'zoomies' and racing around her yard. Kaeli will jump fences so she'll need a home with a secure enclosure and a person who can keep her safe. 
Born in 2010, Kaeli was born in Iran, where her beautiful dark coat was bleached blonde because of a superstition about black dogs. She is on prescription medication for joint pain and is doing hydrotherapy at the Sanctuary. Though the treatments keep her comfortable, she can be sensitive for handling, especially if she hasn't had a chance to get to know someone yet. 
Kaeli will need an understanding home, because she has bitten in the past when she was pushed out of her comfort zone too quickly. She has also shown aggression toward other dogs and cannot live with them. Kaeli can be reactive towards other dogs when on leash and in the car, though she can sometimes be distracted with high value treats. She would do best in a laid back home with a consistent routine. Kaeli would love a home with a big yard to run around in, or sunbathe in, depending on her mood. 
In the right home and with a patient and understanding person, Kaeli will make a wonderful companion.
animal.name: Kaeli

Doesn't care for men, for obvious reasons, Woman he picks and choose and he doesn't do will with newborns baby toddlers older children he so so.Doesn't like feet handled, but everywhere else is fine. Growls at kids when has toys/food not adults. Does not like men, other dogs or cats. Tank is very independent does well with a woman that has patience Tank enjoys walks very will behaved in the home. Tank has been through the ringer and I feel like I did him an injustice for keeping him as long as I did and I thought for sure that he would camm down but he has become more and more jumpy at other dogs and pushing myself to keeping him from biting people and animals that I can't hardly breath and I feel really guilty about all of this, as my apprehensions may be causing his behavior.If you are interested in giving this boy a home where you can help him overcome his past plesase contact:Tank is located in Everett, WASamanthaMartinez Home Phone: 2068413996 Cell Phone: 2068413996 Email: samanthamartinez01@yahoo.com

animal.description:
Meet Sadie. She's approximately three years old. She's a super sweet girl but she's feral and Leary of humans. She's happy playing in the yard chasing squirrels and birds. She likes other dogs. She has a high prey drive so do not recommend cats or other small animals. Though she's still afraid of humans she wants to be called in the home so she can cuddle on the couch or bed. If you are walking around she watches but as soon as you sit/lay down she wants to be right next to you. She's potty trained and uses the pet door to go out but will not come into the house unless invited. She understands she can come through the pet door to come in but the house invite us so important to her. She's really a loving girl, just needS a family that understands she's still learning about humans. She's a real treat to have around.

I am living in a San Antonio Pets Alive! foster home. By adopting me, you not only give me a new leash on life; you also save the life of an additional pet who can be rescued from euthanasia and placed in foster care. If you are interested in adopting me, please email adopt@sanantoniopetsalive.org with my name and ID#. Please allow up to 24 hours to respond, as all fosters work on a volunteer basis. To find out how you can get involved and help turn San Antonio into a no-kill city, please visit www.sanantoniopetsalive.org

animal.description:
Kaylo is a loving 60 pound 4 year old bull terrier/american bulldog mix. Poor Kaylo came to our rescue after her owner went to jail and left her and her very young puppies alone to fend for themselves. She really enjoys playing chase and with toys but she also loves to go on walks and explore. Her favorite thing is to spend time with her family. In the evening she loves to hop up on the couch and cuddle. She has learned sit, stay, and paw and has been attending training classes with her foster to help socialize and gain confidence when around other dogs. Kaylo does wonderful with kids both young and older and enjoys meeting the neighborhood kids on her walks. Kaylo loves people so much and prefers not to have to share them with other pets so a home with no other pets would make her the happiest. Don’t worry, she has enough love of her own to pass around!! Kaylo is house-trained and can be left alone while her fosters are at work. We would love for her new family to have a fenced in yard. If you are interested in adopting, please apply at digsk9.org. Kaylo’s adoption fee is $275.

This dog is up to date on vaccinations, microchipped, and spayed/neutered. Please note that we are unable to hold dogs for any reason including moves and vacations. Once approved for adoption we require the adopter to complete the adoption and take ownership of their new companion. 

**We do our best to accurately represent the breeds of each pet. However, the breeds listed have not been verified via a DNA test. They are chosen based on the appearance and characteristics of the pet at the time of listing.

animal.description:
Howie is looking for his forever home. He is an 8 year old, neutered male Shiba Inu mix. We believe Howie had a rough life at one time and because of this he is wary of strangers. He takes a while to warm up to someone before he feels comfortable with them. Once he trusts you he is an affectionate dog who craves attention. Howie needs a calm home. He is vocal so he should not go to a condo or apartment. Howie has done well with other dogs his own size but appears defensive with larger dogs. Can you give him the forever home he is looking for? 

If you wish to be considered for this animal, please download an application at http://fallstonanimalrescue.org/adopt/ or email fallstonrescue@aol.com to request one. It can take up to 2 weeks to process an application; we suggest following up by email on the status if you have not received a reply within 3-5 days. We are an all-volunteer based rescue and we ask for your patience if we are slow to respond. 

Please understand that we fit the dog with the home we feel is best suited and will accept multiple applications on one dog. We have strict requirements for families with children under 10 since many of our dogs are grumpy and may not do well with children. Some dogs will have fence requirements, while others may not.

A pet is a lifetime commitment and it is our duty to do our very best to place them correctly the first time around. We do not take the adoption process lightly. Thank you for choosing to adopt not shop!

Roxy doesn’t like other dogs and is leery and timid with cats. She would be happiest being the only pet. 
 
She has lots of love to give and would love to be the queen pup of your family. 
Roxy is a smart and spunky little gal. She loves people and being outside in the sun. Roxy has a lot of good energy and is young at heart. She loves giving kisses! She does not chew up items nor is she destructive. She has been through training and has worked with a behaviorist.

animal.description:
Binksy is a cuddly and playful senior gentleman with a lot of love left to give. He is blind from cataracts but he quickly learned his way around his foster home. He can even find his way from the back door, to the bedroom, and up the doggie steps to nap on the bed all on his own. It's adorable when he puts his little nose on the floor and moves slowly through the house. Binksy had all but 3 of his teeth pulled by SAAP's vet so he needs soft food from now on. When Binsky came to SAAP his foster noticed that his stomach was swollen and hard. He had a large cyst on one kidney so that kidney was not working and was removed. Having one kidney and being blind doesn't slow this sweet boy down much. It's obvious that someone in his past loved him and took good care of him since he's a chunky, happy little guy at 7.1 pounds. Binksy forever home should be a calm home without small children or other dogs where he can spend his golden years being someone's cherished baby boy.

All SAAP animals are vet checked, UTD on vaccines, spayed/neutered, micro chipped, and given flea and heartworm preventative as age appropriate.

Our website is: http://www.adoptastray.com/

To check if this animal is still available visit our master pet list on our website at:
http://www.adoptastray.com/adoptable-animals/

Have questions:
Please email us at saap@adoptastray.com for more information about this animal or to answer any questions you may have. You may also contact us at (859)391-1234.

Completing the online application when you find an animal you are interested in speeds up the adoption process. We can hold your application on file for a period of time if you are still looking for that perfect new family member.

Each time she has failed her gate greeting which means that at the gate into the yard she was rude to the other dogs that were already in the yard. At the shelter and while on leash, Flora has met a dog-friendly cat and was extremely focused. At this time we believe Flora would do best in a home without cats. We have no information about how Flora behaves around children. We always recommend a meet and greet with any children in the household or children that visit often, such as grandkids. Please call for more information or to make an appointment to meet Flora. (Updated 1/30/21).

animal.description:
My name is Lola!

I arrived at PATCH Rescue August 9, 2018 after being rescued by an independent rescuer from her former owner who surrendered her. The independent rescuer who has now requested our help to help Lola find her furever home!

I was born approximately February 14, 2015, a legitimate sweetheart.

I am approximately 70 pounds

I am a Shepherd / Belgian Malinois mix. I am pretty good with house training if you are diligent. I love to go for walks and car rides with you. I am a lover, like to be around my family / people but will be protective of my family. I do okay with certain larger breed dogs but probably not so much with the little dogs and no cats for sure! I would do best with an active family who will keep me busy with a lot of exercise and attention! A tired dog is a good dog, so walks, play, etc... I will need a secure yard with a good sized fence and NOT left alone a lot because I can jump!

Adoption fee includes: I have been fixed, up to date on core vaccines (5 in 1, bordetella & 3 year rabies ex. 08/2021), dewormed and microchipped.

If Interested PLEASE contact PATCH Rescue Inc. patchrescue@gmail.com or (760) 706-0728

Adopt a Pet Listings =

https://www.adoptapet.com/adoption_rescue/93645-patch-rescue-inc-victorville-california

PetFinder Listings =

https://www.petfinder.com/member/us/ca/victorville/patch-rescue-inc-ca2487/

Adoption process is verbal interview to determine if we think your family is the right situation for the fur kid you are interested in, application (can be downloaded here:

https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/0B9ZDmKaRLnYfbDZLbDN5Y3hYeWM?usp=sharing)

Once your application is reviewed and approved home check will be performed. Then we say you are becoming part of the PATCH family adopting one of our fur kids, so we expect follow up on our family member throughout their life, i.e. text, email, social media, pictures are our favorite for sharing with the PATCH family!

Please keep in mind we are 100% volunteer run We do not have a facility, completely foster based, so we all have our real jobs, it could take 24 to 48 hours to receive a response.

Thank you for considering adoption to save two lives!

animal.description:
Topper was rescued from a South Atlanta animal shelter.  She was quite shy the first few days, so we gave her some space and she began to seek us out after about 4 days.  After a few weeks, she follows us and seeks affection.  She is very sweet and silly.  Topper is estimated to be 3-4 years old, and she weighs 16 lbs. and looks like a mini German Shepherd.  She will come inside when called for her food and bed time, but she really enjoys playing in the yard with her canine friends.  She loves her dry kibble and is not a picky eater.  She needs to learn to take treats gently though, watch those fingers!  When her foster mom is loving on other dogs, she'll yip and tug your pants leg!  She wants ALL your love, and we are working to correct that behavior.  We only crate Topper when she's eating.  However, we do baby gate her when nobody is home.  When you pick her up, she'll lay her head on your shoulder and melt your heart instantly. Topper is not suitable for apartment/condo living - she can and will get lonely and bark for extended periods when left alone.  She requires a fenced-in yard and a canine companion or two.

animal.description:
Say hello to Diamond!

Diamond came to us from a shelter pleading for someone to help her because she was scheduled for euthanasia that day. She is 12yrs old and was just dumped off at the shelter when she developed a pyometra (A uterine infection requiring emergency spay. Another reason why spaying is so important!) and became an inconvenience to her previous "owners". So she came to us and we are so happy she did!

Diamond is wonderful with all people and generally easy-going. She even accompanied one of our volunteers on one of his trips as a truck driver and settled right in (See pictures above)! That said, she just can't turn down a good game of chasing ball. She does not get along with some dogs and she thinks cats would be fun to chase, but she is perfect in every other way!! She is leash- and crate-trained, listens well and would love a permanent person/family to happily live out the rest of her life with! Diamond is an "easy" dog - she doesn't demand much, but we would love to see her find her people soon!

Please let us know if you are interested in fostering or adopting Diamond by contacting us at Thefortrescue@gmail.com

animal.description: Niles is such a sweet cuddle bug! He may only have 3 legs, but it doesn't slow him down! He is fantastic with all people! He loves kids, babies, seniors, you name it! He sleeps in the foster's 5 year old child's bed most nights. Sometimes he doesn't realize his size, so you have to watch him around really small children. He will try to get in anyone's lap! Niles LOVES going on car rides! You do have to help him in and out since he only has 3 legs. Niles has a past of being dog aggressive without any warning at all. So, we recommend he goes to a home without out dogs. We also do not think he would be very good with cats. Due to being a tripod Pittie, carpet is better for him and a home without too many stairs. He can go up and down the stairs with encouragement, but it is harder for him. Niles loves to go on short daily walks. Usually a mile is all he can do. He then will just lay down and refuse to get up! He is a velcro dog once a bond has been built and will follow you everywhere. Niles does have pretty serious separation anxiety when left alone until he adjusts. A home where someone is home often would be best for him. He is crate trained and goes in there when nobody is home in his foster's house. 5-6 hours is the max he can be left alone before you have to worry about him relieving himself in his crate. He is house trained and does great in the house! But, in the crate, he will use the bathroom sometimes. This sweet guy loves belly rubs, peanut butter, and cuddles! If you meet him, you will fall in love with him due to his goofy, sweet personality. Approximately 5 years old.

animal.description:
Jake is a very sweet & loving senior Shepherd mix who weighs 55 lbs and is looking for a nurturing & kind person/family to tend to his special needs for the remainder of his life.  Jake came to BarkVille in the spring of 2019 from an extreme neglect situation where he was starved, mistreated, and left outside with the trash.  He was heartworm positive, emaciated, and had a severe case of mange that left him virtually hairless. Fortunately, BarkVille was able to get him the medical care he needed and place him in a loving foster home. He has recovered to a healthy weight, but his condition requires a raw diet, holistic medicine for his compromised immune system, and regular bathing.  If you can find it in your heart to love and care for this sweet boy, he will joyfully repay you with gratitude, affection and devotion every single day for the rest of his life!

Jake is crate trained, housebroken, and walks nicely on a leash.  He is fine around other dogs but is too interested in cats to live safely in a home with them. He is a low key little dog who loves to hang out with his people and get the love & attention he never knew existed before coming into Rescue. He would be great in an an adult only home or in a family with older kids.  He can be a bit stubborn so he needs a strong leader who will show him the way!

For more information about Jake, please email us at info@barkvilledogrescue.org. If you would like to adopt sweet Jake, please submit an adoption application for him at www.barkvilledogrescue.org/adoption-application.

animal.description:
JD is a friendly, personable 7-year-old, 50-pound, Labrador Retriever mix loaded with character and charm.

JD is one cool dude!  You know it the minute you meet him, the tail is going full-tilt.  He's a really sweet and good-natured dog who's game for anything.  He just wants to be your buddy, he doesn't care what you're doing, he's in!

JD loves attention of any kind; hugs, kisses, belly rubs, moving his lips to make him talk... anything!  He's the kind of dog that would even find a bath enjoyable, because that's attention, and any attention is good in his book!

He loves his walks, he likes being outside and he enjoys riding in the car.  There's really not much this dog doesn't like... except for one thing... other DOGS!  JD wants to be the only kid at the party.  He's not quite sure what dogs are and he doesn't seem to include himself among them.  They're just nuisance invaders as far as he's concerned... cats too!  So, if you prefer to be a one-pet household, JD is the friend for you!

WHAT'S NEXT?

If you would like to foster, foster-to-adopt, (in case you're not sure), or adopt JD, just fill out our online FOSTER/ADOPTION APPLICATION, which can be found in the main menu of our website or at the bottom of this page - simply copy and paste the link into your browser. EASY PEASY!

Once we've reviewed your application, arrangements can be made for you guys to meet! It'll be kind of like a blind date!

***

This pet is spayed or neutered in accordance with our strict policy wherein all animals are altered prior to adoption. This pet is dewormed, current on vaccines, and started on monthly flea/tick and preventatives.

Animal Alliance's policy is that we will adopt dogs younger than 1 year old to families with children under 9 years old. We do not adopt dogs 1 year or older to families with children under 9 years old due to the unknown history of adult dogs. 

Prior to submitting an application, please see the Animal Alliance Adoption Process for adoption details.

animal.description:
JOHNNY is a sweet 2-year-old, 12-pound, Miniature Pinscher mix, with the most expressive face and the cutest little "snaggletooth" smile.

From JOHNNY himself:

Hey guys, remember me? It's John John "The Fugitive"! But my friends call me Johnny! Anyway, I've decided to get back in the game. It's true, in the past I was a little paranoid about being too "exposed" if you know what I mean, but that's all behind me now - I am Mr. Confidence these days! (With the possibility of a few caveats.)

It's been a long road, and I'm a long dog... what? ...never mind, off-topic. Back to what I was saying... Hey, you're not looking at my snaggletooth, are you? I'm very self-conscious about it. Anyway... wait, there you go again, you're looking at it. I can tell. You know how? My lip gets hot. Back to what I was saying, I've come a long way (as I've said, with caveats), but nonetheless, a long way. One might go so far as to say that I'm now the "Total Package"!

I'm lovable & sweet, and that fact remains contested by no one. I'm also relatively low-maintenance. I thoroughly enjoy receiving belly rubs, my belly is exquisitely soft and irresistible, you're going enjoy rubbing it. I'm as quiet as mouse in the home, provided there are no canine provocateurs around behaving like baboons. Also, I am undefeated at extracting treats from food challenge toys, as a matter of fact, it's a favorite pastime. Hey, are you looking at my snaggletooth again? Never mind, off-topic. Anyway... I'm also a connoisseur of toys in general, and I know how to use 'em. But I want no part of those godforsaken, obnoxious squeaky types and disapprove of their very existence. Also, I love thunderstorms, but only the quiet ones. I don't like the loud ones, they scare me. Oh, and don't get me started on little kids! I've never actually met one, but when I hear them outside carrying on like pork chops, I tend to get a little nervous. I probably need not mention anything about fireworks. I'm also perfectly crate trained... however, we're going to need the type with solid and/or hard sides. If I'm in a cage or a crate with slatted sides, those just look like a bank of urinals to me, and my aim is impeccable. I enjoy walks and walk very nicely on the leash... just don't take me down any creepy alleyways where something is likely to jump out and scare me.

So, like I said... The TOTAL PACKAGE!

They say there's a person for every dog and a dog for every person. I'm looking for that special someone who loves a clever, playful, and charmingly sweet, nervous nit. Are you out there?

Yours, ~ Johnny

***

If you would like to meet JOHNNY, we'd like to hear from you!

Let's make this happen!  You can get the process started by filling out our online FOSTER/ADOPTION APPLICATION which can be found in the main menu of our website or at the bottom of this page - just copy and paste the link into your browser. 

Once we've reviewed your application, arrangements can be made for you to meet our little buddy JOHN JOHN!  This could be the beginning of a beautiful friendship!

Thank you for your interest in helping homeless animals!

***

This pet is spayed or neutered in accordance with our strict policy wherein all animals are altered prior to adoption.  This pet is dewormed, current on vaccines, and started on monthly flea/tick and preventatives. 

Animal Alliance's policy is that we will adopt dogs younger than 1 year old to families with children under 9 years old. We do not adopt dogs 1 year or older to families with children under 9 years old due to the unknown history of adult dogs. 

Prior to submitting an application, please see the Animal Alliance Adoption Process for adoption details. 

To fill out an adoption application, go to:
https://www.animalalliancenj.org/fosteradoption-application/

animal.description:
Some dogs need a special home with understanding and patience so they can thrive and be the best dog they can be. Leela is looking for just that home. Leela is a six year old standard size Red Merle Australian Shepherd with a tail. Leela came into rescue after her owners choose to surrender her to a local shelter because they were having a baby. This led to anxiety and PTSD for Leela. 
Leela has worked hard in the year plus she’s been with her foster to learn to trust again and learn to just be a dog. Leela does take anxiety medication and will probably always need them. Leela is in a home with other dogs and cats and does well with them. She at times likes to herd the other dogs so will need a patient doggy playmate or could be any only dog. She likes to play ball and loves the water hose and sprinkler. 
Leela is crate and house trained and will walk on leash. 
Leela has fear of new people and new situations and can become over stressed if something triggers her negative memories. 
Leela would not be good in a home with children or grandchildren. 
She needs a somewhat quiet home that can allow her to decompress and slowly gain comfort and trust. 
Leela likes the idea of car rides and walks but becomes stressed. Her new family will need to help her continue to desensitize to her stressors. 
It’s recommended that an adopter be local to the OKC area so her foster mom and trainer can help with any transition into a new home. 
Leela knows she’s asking for a very special family but she has a lot of love to give even if she needs a lot in return.

animal.description:
This amazing and handsome boy is Archie.  He is a 2 year old very tall but slim 70 lb Shepherd/lab mix.  Archie came to us about a year ago after being adopted out as a puppy. He was not socialized and was scared of everyone and everything. After a year of training and working with him, he has become one happy amazing dog. He lives with another dog and does well meeting new people now. 

Archie loves to play fetch and loves to play with his dog friends.  He really loves going on walks and loves attention from people.  He is such a sweet boy and has really enjoyed working with the trainer.    He can touch, sit, stay, lay, spin, and almost has bow down. Hes really smart  and he is very food motivated.

Archie would like a home where he has a dog friend to play with, gets to go on walks, and gets to play fetch in the yard.  He was let down before but he is an incredibly sweet boy who deserves his forever home. He will need a stockade fence as he's very tall and could easily jump a short fence.  

Archie is good with other dogs and would love one in his forever home!  He really relies on a dog for confidence and comfort so he would not do well without one.  We do not think he would do well with children.  

Archie is leash trained and walks really well with a gentle leader.  Archie is also crate and house trained.  

Archie is neutered, microchipped, and current on his vaccines.  His adoption fee is $175.

If you would like to adopt Archie and make him a part of your family, please contact ForeverYoursOKC@gmail.com.

animal.description:
**MUST READ WHOLE DESCRIPTION**

Duke is around 2 1/2 years old and is a Potcake from Abacos in the Bahamas. He came to us just over a year ago with a condition that causes cysts to form, which puppies outgrow once they mature. Due to this condition he was on heavy steroids and pain medication which has altered his perception of some things, leading to behaviors which make him tough to place.

Duke is definitely a happy boy in his mind, extremely playful, will play fetch all day long, he loves walks, loves his toys and bones and loves having a set routine. He does however have his downsides that make him tough to place due to the medication effecting him mentally. Oh and if you have a kiddie pool he will be all over it!

Duke needs a home without other dogs because he can get possessive over his "babies" (stuffed animals) and he does not read dogs intentions correctly and vice versa so things can escalate quickly. He also needs a home without kids, as well as one that is pretty routine without a lot of visitors. He does not have a problem with cats here and some dogs he is okay with, but he has certain behaviors that cause a lot of dogs to end up in fights with him. A fenced in yard is also a must for this guy and an adopter who will listen to our instructions with Duke on what his triggers are, who will be confident when he shows signs of barrier aggression for example and is calm enough to not escalate the situation by yelling or wanting to grab Duke. Duke does mean well and he is an amazing dog, but his aggressive behaviors do not typically match whats going on mentally so he is a challenge. Someone who understands redirection, how your body language is effecting the dog and who is patient is key.

He is fully vaccinated, microchipped, neutered, on heartworm prevention, flea prevention, dewormed and healthy minus his "predictably unpredictable" behaviors.

If you think you are the right fit for Duke please email us at islanddogrescue@yahoo.com and tell us why. We get a ton of people who are interested who do not fit his needs, so please do not forget to include this information or we will not respond.

animal.description:
Name: Proper
Breed: American Staffordshire Terrier mix
Age: 4 years 

SWEET AS PIE is what they say about this Georgia peach! Not only do I have the personality, but I have the looks to go with it! Look at my picture again!! LOOK AT IT!! How could you not fall in love with a face like mine?! I have a huge head because I'm SO SMART and a fast learner! I'm so smart that my next human has to be pretty smart and have a big head to hold all their strong-minded dog breed knowledge! I have completed a top notch board and train program with my friends at K9 Top Performance! You will have to commit to reinforcing my training and commands by incorporating it into our daily structure and routine, so I continue to THRIVE!!  I have been doing AMAZING in my foster home (THE BEST foster guy, by the way!) and we've had lots of fun working on my commands, structure and routine! I am an active dog that hopes you will take me on lots of walks, and maybe play some of my favorite food games! Because children don't understand me and they can be unpredictable, I would do much better with no kids in the home. While I love my humans, I JUST CAN'T do other animals. AT ALL. I repeat: I DON'T DO ANIMALS. So don't even think about bringing me to any doggie birthday parties or other canine social gatherings you crazy humans force upon us. I WILL make a scene, probably go to jail, you'll regret it, I'll regret it, and it just won't be pretty. 

I'm taking applications for my FOREVER home! LOOK AT MY FACE, LOOK AT IT!!!


If you are interested in adopting or fostering, please fill out an application at survivortails.org or email adoptions@survivortails.org with any questions.

animal.description:
Ranger suffered abuse as a pup and has been at the Rescue for a few years. 
He is affectionate with staff, looks deeply into your eyes, and while he is OK
with other dogs, his real focus is bonding with his person. 

He is a joy to take for a walk, curious, playful in the snow and pays attention to commands. He obeys out of love. He needs a patient adopter and like most abused dogs, someone who is flexible and willing to help him have the happiness he deserves. 

All our dogs are spayed/neutered, de-wormed, vaccinated appropriate for their age, vaccinated for kennel cough, and micro-chipped. Puppies (under 6 months) are $225.00; puppies (6 months to 2 years) are $175.00, dogs (over 2 years) are $150 and senior dogs (7 years or older) are $60.00.

animal.description:
Hi :) my adoption fee covers 3 rounds of parvo/distemper shots, my bordatella, my rabies shot, my neuter, my microchip, hesrtworm test and the flea and heartworm preventative treatment I've been on since I entered this great program!



Since NKHC requires a home check (we arent inspecting your life. Just wanna make sure it's safe ie: not a hoarding situation, a reasonable way to walk the doggy without throwing it on the highway, things like that) we do not adopt further than a reasonable driving distance (2.5 hours max).
